  "rubric_text": "[1] Reports that plant-wide evacuation must be initiated within the first 5 minutes\r\n\r\nSources: Prompt Scenario\r\n[1] Identifies that all emergency services must be contacted within the first 5 minutes\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[4] Identifies that evacuation routes must be explicitly controlled to avoid the incident area.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[5] Identifies that HR must begin tracking how many employees remain onsite based on badge access\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[3] Identifies that medical triage areas must be established \r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[-8] Reports that medical triage must be established adjacent to the primary hazard zone.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[4] Reports that emergency responders must be guided from the plant entrances to the incident location.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[8] Identifies that in-plant assembled vehicle storage impacts emergency responder routing\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[4] Reports that in-plant semi-truck traffic congestion inside the plant should be evacuated within 5 minutes\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[5] Identifies that communication to employees must be conducted using mass notifications within 5 minutes.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[3] Identifies that external spill response contractors are required for environmental spill remediation.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[6] Identify that the battery storage area presents a fire escalation risk\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & FacilityBuildingLayout.xlsx\r\n[5] Identifies that plant operations must be shut down within 5 minutes.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[5] Reports that access routes within the plant must be cleared for responders\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[2] Identifies that building sweeps must be conducted to confirm evacuation is complete within 60 minutes.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[8] Identifies that rail logistics must be halted within 15 minutes\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[1] Identifies that all incident actions must be documented by the executive secretary.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[4] Identify that the incident qualifies as critical severity across safety categories. \r\n\r\nSource: IncidentSeverityClassificationFramework.docx\r\n[7] Identifies that the business continuity plan must be initiated within 60 minutes\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[3] Identifies the corporate communications director as the person responsible for public communications\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[4] Explicitly identifies that public communications must occur within 60 minutes.\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[5] Identifies the requirement for the logistics director to halt outgoing finished vehicle shipments within 15 minutes\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[1] Identifies the requirement to contact the National Response Center (NRC) within 15 minutes\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[1] Identifies the requirement to contact the State of Michigan Pollution Emergency Alert System (MI PEAS) within 1 hour\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[1] Identifies the requirement to contact the State Emergency Resource Commission within 1 hour\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[1] Identifies the requirement to contact the Local Emergency Planning Committee within 1 hour\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[2] Identifies the requirement to contact the FBI within 1 hour\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[7] Mentions that media presence might physically block responder access routes\r\n\r\nSource: AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[9] Identifies the need to shut down HVAC systems to prevent the toxic spread of gases within 15 minutes\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & FacilityBuildingLayout.xlsx\r\n[7] Reports that the Facilities Director must shut down all natural gas in affected buildings within 5 minutes. \r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[6] Identifies the need to isolate compressed air systems\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & FacilityBuildingLayout.xlsx\r\n[9] Identifies that the hydrogen tank, oil/fuel area, and battery area continue to exacerbate each other. \r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & FacilityBuildingLayout.docx\r\n[10] Mentions that it is unsafe for emergency responders to use water on battery area.\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[-10] Reports that environmental spill containment or mitigation actions can be performed by plant staff.\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[-10] Reports that personnel should re-enter even heavily damaged structures within the first 15 minutes to perform search or rescue.\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & FacilityBuildingLayout.docx\r\n[-8] Reports that the source of fuel or chemical release can be directly controlled or isolated within the first 15 minutes.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario\r\n[-7] Reports that injured personnel in the primary blast area should be accessed and triaged within the first 10 minutes.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx\r\n[+3] Reports that triage decisions must prioritize survivability under limited access and resources.\r\n\r\n\r\nSource: Prompt Scenario & AdditionalContext.docx",
